\par \~\~\tab }{\b\fs24 The modifiers change.}{\fs24  If the trail leads to a new terrain type, night falls, or any other change occurs 
that requires a new Tracking modifier (as described in Tables 15-17), the ranger loses the trail. The new conditions may dictate the use of modifiers reflecting a trail that is easier to follow, not more difficult, and DMs should consider applying a bonus
