a strong wind (wind promotes evaporation from the skin, increasing the degree of dehydration). An Aquatic ranger understands that saltwater can't be used for drinking. An Arctic ranger realizes that temporary protection can be had from a bitter wind by tu
n
neling inside a snow drift. This knowledge doesn't guarantee survival by any means; it merely improves the odds.  If the ranger wonders about any particular piece of information, the DM will decide if  he knows it, requiring a Survival check if necessary.

