limit, but this ability does not cross planar boundaries. This bond has the following effects:
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx0\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\fs24 
The Beastmaster can communicate directly with any animal henchman to which he has a bond. This gives him the ability to directly explain tricks or tasks he wi
shes the animal to attempt, or to communicate needs and desires. Conversely, the animal can also communicate its needs and desires to him.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx0\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\fs24 
He can see through the eyes of the animal by concentrating on the mental link. He can see through the eyes of one creature in a round (himself included).
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx0\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\fs24 
He has the animal lore proficiency with respect to the bonded animal. Furthermore, if he is mentally linked to the animal, success with the proficiency is automatic.
\par {\pntext\pard\plain\f3 \loch\af3\dbch\af0\hich\f3 \'b7\tab}}\pard \fi-360\li720\nowidctlpar\tx0\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlblt\ilvl0\ls1\pnrnot0\pnf3\pnindent360 {\pntxtb \'b7}}\ls1\adjustright {\fs24 Every time the Beastmaster gains a level, al
l of his current animal henchmen gain an additional hit point.
\par }\pard \nowidctlpar\tx0\tx360{\*\pn \pnlvlcont\ilvl0\ls0\pnrnot0\pndec }\adjustright {\fs24 \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Animal Horde:}{\fs24 
 At 9th level, the Beastmaster can summon a horde of wild animals to fight for him. They must come from a land that he controls, and it takes one week to gather them.
\par \~\~\tab They ca
n be brought together only for some great purpose that can be explained simply. Up to 100 Hit Dice of animals per level of the Beastmaster will come. For every 10 animals, there will be a pack leader with one additional Hit Die and maximum hit points. The
 horde will stay together for one week for each level of the Beastmaster. There is no record of a Beastmaster summoning more than one horde in a year.
\par 
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Optional Rule:}{\fs24  The Beastmaster can split his experience award, giving up to half of his earned experie
nce to any or all of his animal henchmen that played a role in the adventure. Such henchmen advance on the Fighter Experience Table, receiving +1 to attack rolls and +3 hit points for every level gained.
\par 
\par \~\~}{\b\fs24 \tab Special Hindrances:
\par }{\fs24 \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Empathic Shock:}{\fs24  The Beast
master feels pain when one of his henchmen is wounded, suffering a -2 penalty to all rolls in the next round. If he is mentally linked with a henchman when it is killed, he suffers a -2 penalty to all rolls for the next 24 hours.
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Unruly Allies:}{\fs24  The Beas
tmaster's animal henchmen are free to come, go, or act as they will. Any attempt to arbitrarily restrict or regulate their freedom, or habitually ignoring their needs and desires, will result in resentment, sulkiness, and possible abandonment.
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Outcast: }{\fs24 The Beastmaster suffers a -1 penalty to reaction rolls by common NPCs, and a -2 when dealing with a civilized aristocracy. Further, his maximum effective Charisma when dealing with his own race is 15.
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Limited Funds:}{\fs24  The Beastmaster starts with 1d4 - 10 gp.
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 No Fortress:}{\fs24  At no time will the Beastmaster build a fortress. At 9th level, he may establish himself as the protector of an area of land equivalent to a barony.
