d is discolored and laced with tiny cracks).
\par \~\~}{\b\fs24 \tab Special Hindrances:}{\fs24  By moving ahead of the party, the Pathfinder places himself in a position of risk. Separated from his companions, the Pathfinder is more likely to be the victim of enemy attacks. He runs a 
greater risk of drawing fire from snipers, and is more susceptible to ambushes from hostile creatures. If he fails to recognize a hazard, he'll probably be the first to become a victim.
