it will normally submerge unless it makes a successful morale roll. If the morale roll fails, the rider can command the mount to re-surface by making a successful proficiency check. If the check fails, the rider can attempt another check each round therea
fter, so long as he is physically able. While submerged with the mount and attempting to force it to surface, the rider risks drowning (see Chapter 14 of the }{\i\fs24 Player's Handbook}{\fs24 
). Because he's exerting himself, the number of rounds the rider can hold his breath is equal to half his Constitution score.
