\par }{\b\fs24\cf13 Weaponsmithing, Crude
\par }{\fs24 
\par \~\~\tab This proficiency allows the making simple weapons out of natural materials. This skill is most often found in those from a primitive, tribal, or savage background.
\par \~\~\tab The crude weapons are limited to natural materials: stone, wood, bone, sinew, reed, and the like. Crude weapons take a certain amount of time to make. The DM may add additional primitive weapons to the basic list.
\par \~\~\tab The chance for success is based on the character's Wisdom, with a -3 penalty. Any warrior or a character with the hunting proficiency has a +3 bonus. The fashioner must be proficient in the use of the weapon.
\par \~\~\tab If successful, the weapon can be used normally. If failed, the weapon is so badly flawed as to be useless. On a roll of 20, the weapon seems sound, but will break upon first use. On a roll of 1, the weapon has no chance of breaking exce
pt against a harder material.
\par \~\~\tab }{\i\fs24 Optional:}{\fs24  Crude weapons check for breaking upon inflicting damage; roll 1d6. Bone weapons break on a roll of 1 or 2, stone weapons break on a roll of 1.
\par \~\~\tab }{\b\fs24 Crossover groups:}{\fs24  Warrior.
